This project uses the Credit Card Fraud Detection dataset published by the Machine Learning Group on Kaggle.

📌 Source: Kaggle - Credit Card Fraud Detection
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud

🧾 Description:

Contains 19898 credit card transactions made in September 2013 by European cardholders.
Out of all transactions, 492 are frauds (≈ 0.172% of the dataset).

🔐 Anonymized Features:

Features V1 to V28 are the result of a PCA (Principal Component Analysis) transformation to protect confidentiality.
Only Time, Amount, and Class remain in their original form.

🎯 Target Label:

Class = 0: Legitimate transaction
Class = 1: Fraudulent transaction
